first_block.description:
At t={current_time}, selecting shortest remaining time...

Ready queue: {ready_list}

Selected: {process_id} (Remaining burst = {remaining})

no_preemption_equal.description:
Process {new_process} arrives at t={current_time}.

Remaining burst comparison:
- {new_process}: {new_remaining}
- {current_process}: {current_remaining}

EQUAL remaining time → NO preemption!
Current process continues (SRT rule).

process_complete.description:
Process {process_id} finishes execution!

Original Burst: {burst}
Started: t={start_time}, Completed: t={end_time}
Waiting time: {wait_time}
Turnaround time: {tat}

final.description:
SRT Scheduling Complete!

Execution Order: {execution_order}

Metrics:
{metrics}

Average Waiting Time: {avg_wait}
Average Turnaround Time: {avg_tat}

Note: SRT minimizes average waiting time but has high context switch overhead.
